      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So if there's this fundamental difference between a more collectivist culture and our individualistic system, doesn't that create a risk of systemic failure? Like, if the demographic majority shifts toward these different values, aren't we basically looking at the erosion of the very foundations that make Western democracy what it is? It almost sounds like a slow-motion replacement of the governing principles that have defined the West for centuries.",
