      "content": "The concept of \"systemic failure\" is an overstatement; rather, it's a process of adaptation and redefinition. When demographic shifts occur, the underlying assumptions of a society are tested, forcing institutions to evolve or fracture. The current debate is less about replacement and more about whether the established framework can accommodate a wider array of deeply held, non-Western-centric values. This pressure inevitably leads to political realignment and the renegotiation of what \"American\" or \"Western\" democratic principles actually mean in practice.",
